I am super grateful for the fun and awesome cooking session with Natalie @natalieportman. It was so much fun making our favorite food - Dumplings from scratch and they were so yummy.  She is truly an amazing lady with lots of great inspirations. I really appreciate her for using her platform to showcase vegan cooking, please check out her wonderful work on her page. Thank you once again, Natalie! Big hugs to you.

Here is the potsticker recipe that we made together (makes 24 potstickers). Have a beautiful weekend, everyone. Best, WoonHeng
Wrapper - 240 gram all-purpose (plain) flour, 125 ml ( ½ cup) hot water
Filling
- 14 oz (397g) firm tofu drained and pressed
- ¾ cups (75g) shredded cabbage
- 1 small carrot finely chopped
- 2 teaspoons toasted sesame oil
- 1 teaspoon salt
- A few shakes of white pepper
- A couple of handfuls of chopped spring onion and grated fresh ginger

Directions: 
To make the dumpling wrapper, place flour in a bowl and make a well in the middle. Slowly pour in the hot water. Using a spatula or a pair of chopsticks, stir to mix the flour until you get a lumpy well-mixed, or shaggy dough (if there are dry spots of flour in the bowl, add more water, 1 tablespoon at a time). Transfer it onto a cleaned surface and knead it into a rough dough. Cover with a damp towel and let it rest for about 5 mins. Then, knead the dough until a smooth top forms, about 10-12mins; rest for about 30mins.
Filling: Blanch cabbage in hot water for 45secs. Remove and quickly rinse them with cold water. Squeeze out all the liquid and give it a rough chop. Mash pressed tofu and place it into a cheesecloth bag. Wring out as much liquid as possible. Place chopped cabbage and tofu in a mixing bowl along with chopped scallions, carrots, and season with toasted sesame oil, salt, and white pepper, and ginger.
After 30 minutes, divide the dough into 24 equal portions and form them into balls. Roll each one into a thin circular wrapper. Place a filling in the middle and pleat to seal. 
Heat a non-stick pan with oil (adjust based on the size of the pan) then place the dumplings in, slightly apart in one layer. Cook over medium heat until the bottom turns golden brown.

Napa Cabbage Sticky Rice rolls '白菜糯米卷' in sweet and spicy sauce - easy flavorful comfort food made with homegrown long beans and leftover kale stems! Once wrapped, I pan-fried them and then served with a simple sauce for a delicious meal- YUM! Full detailed recipe and video are now up on my blog or check this IGTV for steps. Hope you enjoy this dish as much as I do. Have a wonderful day, friends! Best, WoonHeng

For the full recipe, steps and video, please visit: https://woonheng.com/sticky-rice-cabbage-rolls/

Ingredients
10 - 12 large Napa Cabbage leaves or other veggie of choice
oil for cooking
Cabbage Roll Sauce: 3 slices of ginger, 3-4 medium-sized mushrooms sliced, 2 tablespoons chopped green onions, 1½ tablespoons soy sauce/tamari, 1 tablespoon mirin, ½ tablespoon maple syrup (optional), 1 chopped Thai chilis (optional), salt and pepper to taste, ½ cup water, cornstarch slurry
Filling: 
1 ½ cups sticky or glutinous rice or other sticky grain such as sushi rice
1 cup water
1 cup of chopped veggies used a mixture of long beans, kale stems
1 small carrot chopped
½ tablespoon minced ginger
½ cup mushrooms, sliced used Bella
1 tablespoon soy sauce or tamari
½ tablespoon toasted sesame oil
salt and pepper to taste
Music: YouTube Audio - Faith
.

#wonton #dumpling style 2

Take one wrapper & place it on your palm like a diamond. Spoon 1 teaspoon mixture & put in the middle of wrapper. Dab some water on each end. Bring the middle two ends together, then bring right side by pushing the wrapper to the middle. Repeat for left side. Place wonton in the crease between your thumb and index finger and press to seal. Repeat until you are done with all wrapper.

Easy-baked Curry Potato Bun😋 - It's soft and fluffy filled with spicy potatoes that are perfect for breakfast or your afternoon treat.💗 ⁣Make some ahead to bring to lunch too.👍🏼⁣
Potatoes are delicious in any form, agree😄? They can be pan-fried, steam, baked, or used as a binder in a lot of dishes. Some of my favorite potato dishes include curry potatoes, braised potatoes with carrots, potato balls, and curry puff.⁣ So, when my comfort food mood hits, I want to make a delicious curry potato bun inspired by chicken curry buns from the bakeries in Malaysia.⁣ ⁣
⁣⁣
Full recipe instructions: https://woonheng.com/vegan-baked-curry-potato-bun/⁣
or Google 'woonheng curry potato bun'⁣
⁣⁣
Cooking notes:⁣⁣
- both bread and all-purpose flour works great in this recipe⁣⁣
- for a fluffier bread, add a pinch of baking powder⁣⁣
- okay to skip the softened butter in the dough, just be sure to knead into a soft dough with a smooth top⁣⁣
- for that glaze look, I brush it with melted vegan butter or egg wash (mix 1 tablespoon maple syrup with 2 tablespoons unsweetened oat milk) right after I took it out from the oven. Please note the skin will shrink a little if you apply too much sweet glaze. ⁣
⁣⁣
I hope you give this recipe a try. Have a great Tuesday and for those in Malaysia (Selamat Hari Merdeka). Best, WoonHeng 韵馨❤️⁣⁣

Asian-style vegan roast 'chicken'😋 (Shao Ji) made from king oyster mushroom is so succulent and tasty. The marinated tofu skin (yuba) definitely gives this dish an amazing roasted look that you can't resist having a bite. Using mushrooms as the main ingredient to create that meaty texture has been around since I was a kid. This includes mutton made from mushrooms stem, chicken satay made from lion's mane mushrooms, and many many more. This dish is often served with flavored rice (google 'woonheng char siu fan') but you can simply serve it with a side of homemade ginger garlic sauce (google 'woonheng ginger garlic sauce').⁣
⁣
Full recipe instructions with long video: https://woonheng.com/asian-style-vegan-roast-chicken/⁣
or watch it on my YouTube channel⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- large King oyster mushrooms or trumpet (eryngii) works the best in the recipe, try to get similar size if you can⁣
- You can keep the whole stem (google 'woonheng lemon chicken') or remove the cap for other dishes⁣
- The ingredients are simple and I have the detailed steps in the video and instructions, please check it out. ⁣
⁣
I hope you give this recipe a try (inspired by Vegepapa on YouTube) and have a fantastic weekend. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨💗⁣⁣

Vegan Shanghai shao mai😋 (sticky rice dumpling), 上海烧卖 is now live @Food52 website. Shanghai shao mai have a distinct look that resembles a vase, with a round bottom, slender middle, and wide opening at the top. From the side angle, the top looks like a bouquet of flowers, don't you think?😁⁣
⁣
Recipe: https://food52.com/recipes/86331-shanghai-shao-mai-vegan-recipe ⁣
⁣⁣
Cooking notes:⁣⁣
- I used store-bought dumpling wrappers this time instead of from scratch-dough⁣
- Prepare the sticky rice as directed, I soaked mine overnight (before bed) and steamed it the next day⁣
- The wrapping method is a little different and very fun to make⁣
⁣⁣
I hope you give this dish a try. Have a great Thursday! Best, WoonHeng 韵馨⁣💜⁣⁣⁣

Teriyaki tofu balls😋, are so good and easy to make - tag your friends to make some this week! This recipe is easy and simple with a scrumptious sticky sauce. The tofu balls are made from firm tofu that has a great crunch from vegetables stems and nuts. They are great as baked, air-fried, or fried. Tofu is a great binding agent especially after you have removed the liquid. It will turn into a mashed paste and when pair with finely chopped vegetables, you can make it into patties or balls. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Full recipe instructions: https://woonheng.com/vegan-teriyaki-tofu-balls/⁣⁣
or Google 'woonheng tofu teriyaki balls'⁣
⁣⁣
Cooking notes:⁣⁣
- I used a nut milk bag to squeeze the tofu to mash it up while removing the liquid. Check out the video on how it looks like after I've removed the liquid.⁣⁣⁣
- Finely chop the vegetables so they bind better⁣
- Use other nuts or skip nuts if you can't have it⁣
- Only add enough cornstarch to bind them.⁣⁣⁣
- For complete allium-free, use cilantro as a garnish instead.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Super thankful to all of you who made this dish and sent me a note on my DM and left a sweet message on my blog - Thank YOU! Have a beautiful day. Stay safe and well. Best, Woon Heng 韵馨💗⁣⁣

Vegan sweet and sour 'fish'😋is absolutely appetizing with that tangy sauce. In the past, I wrapped the 'fish' with tofu skin and today, you can try it with rice paper (Vietnamese spring roll wrapper). Please check my website for tips and how it's done.⁣
⁣
Full recipe: https://woonheng.com/vegan-sweet-and-sour-fish/⁣
or search 'sweet and sour fish' on woonheng.com⁣
or watch my new YouTube video (with voiceover🤗)⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- Firm tofu needs to be drained properly before adding to the mix⁣
- Do not pack the rolls tightly when you roll it, leave some gaps. The filling will expand and burst open if it's too tight⁣
- Use a serrated knife to slice the rolls⁣
- Pan-fry the open side (with tofu filling) ⁣
⁣
I hope you give this dish a try and visit my blog or youtube to support me.☺️Have a beautiful weekend. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨💗⁣⁣

Vegan Rad Na😋- a delicious flat rice noodle in thick gravy! It features silky homemade flat rice noodles that were pan-fried for maximum wok aroma and then drenched in a mouthwatering umami savoriness gravy.🤩When I first tried this noodle dish, it reminded me of wat tan hor (Cantonese-style flat rice noodles) from Malaysia. They both feature the same silky noodles and slurpable gravy, but wat tan hor is on the saltier side and usually has eggs in the gravy. ⁣
⁣
Full recipe instructions and long video: https://woonheng.com/vegan-rad-na/⁣
or Google 'woonheng rad na'⁣
⁣⁣
Cooking notes:⁣⁣
- These flat rice noodles are homemade but you can use a store-bought fresh precut version as well.⁣
- Coating the noodles with sauce first before pan-frying gives the noodles an even color.⁣⁣
- Yes, you can sub with gluten-free sauces if needed⁣⁣
- Fermented soybean paste - I'm used Master brand - check my blog for pic⁣ or try taucu ⁣
- I used veggie stock and not broth. If you can't find veggie stock, you can mix the desired mushrooms seasoning or umami seasoning with water to create a simple quick stock. Or please check highlight on how I make veggie stock. ⁣⁣
- The condiment shown is a simple chopped Thai chile with vegan fish sauce (nước mắm Chay - recipe on my blog as well)⁣⁣
⁣
Have a wonderful Thursday! Best, WoonHeng  韵馨💗⁣

Black pepper cauliflower💗 is scrumptious and packed with wonderful flavors from freshly pounded peppercorns. Each bite comes with a buttery taste, peppery heat, and aromatic herbs. I forgot how many bowls of rice I ate this with.🙈😋⁣
⁣
Full recipe instructions and long video: https://woonheng.com/vegan-black-pepper-crab/⁣
or Google 'woonheng black pepper crab'⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- When you make your batter, test to be sure the coat the floret without much dripping. It's normal for the batter to thin out over time especially if your florets are not dry enough. If that happens, just add a little more flour to the batter and remix before you dredge the floret in it.⁣
- This black pepper sauce has heat but peppery heat, so feel free to up the heat with more chile if you like. ⁣
- Curry leaf is optional but once you temper it with the sauce, it gives this dish an amazing aroma. ⁣
⁣
I hope you give this dish a try. Have a great start to your new week, be safe! Best, WoonHeng 韵馨💗⁣

This Thai basil pancake😋 (九層塔抓饼 jiǔ céng tǎ Zhua bing) has an amazing flaky texture and is so aromatic. Ever since I shared my cong you zhua bing (hand grasps scallion pancake), my mom reminded me that she loves the version with Thai basil and misses it. She hasn't visited this stall in a long time, hope the owner is doing okay🙏🏼. I made it using a combination of my roti canai (roti paratha) and scallion pancake recipes. The result is a delicious and flavorful pancake that is perfect for any meal of the day! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Full recipe instructions and video: https://woonheng.com/thai-basil-pancake-zhua-bing/⁣⁣
or search 'thai basil pancake' on woonheng.com⁣⁣
or watch it on Youtube⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Please check my blog for detailed instructions, tips, and storage notes.⁣⁣
Cooking notes:⁣⁣
- As usual, I tried to include as many steps as possible into a short video, please check my long video for the complete process⁣⁣
- Yes, you can make the dough ahead of time and refrigerate but use oil that won't solidify easily. When ready, thaw the dough to room temp before stretching⁣⁣
- The fan folding method is from my roti canai's recipe and will definitely work on the toss and flip method as most seller does back at home😁⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I hope you give this dish a try especially you have lots of Thai basil now.🙌🏼Have a fantastic and safe weekend.  Best, WoonHeng 韵馨💗⁣⁣⁣

node.text:
Kon Lo Hor Fun or Dry Toss Flat Rice Noodle🤤 recipe is live @Food52 website. This dish is absolutely delicious for breakfast and super easy to make, especially if you have ready-made hor fun in your pantry. Kon Lo is a Cantonese word that translates to dry toss. One of the most popular dishes is kon lo mee. It's a simple and quick meal that I love to make to switch up my normal routine. ⁣
⁣
Recipe: https://food52.com/recipes/86228-rice-noodles-mushrooms-scallions-chile-oil-recipe⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- This recipe works well with rice vermicelli (bihun) as well. Simply cook the noodles as directed and toss with the sauce for a delicious meal⁣
- Add your favorite protein or blanched vegetables if preferred⁣
- I made the shallot oil from scratch but if you are using pre-made, please heat it up before you mix it with the sauces⁣
⁣
I hope you give this dish a try. Have a great Thursday! Best, WoonHeng 韵馨⁣💜⁣⁣

node.text:
San Bei Tofu💕 (Three-cup tofu) is my favorite dish to make for lunch or dinner (probably at least once a week). This recipe is so flavorful and packed with aromatic Thai basil. You can choose to pan-fry or air-fry the tofu, both ways shared on my blog. I actually added another step for the air-fried tofu recipe (you can use the same step for pan-fried as well) where I finished off in a claypot. Give it a try if you like it this way or simply simmer the tofu in the pan until all sauce has been absorbed.⁣
⁣
Full recipe instructions with long video: https://woonheng.com/three-cup-san-bei-tofu/⁣
or Google 'woonheng three cup tofu'⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- Adjust your tofu cooking time based on the texture. If you get medium firm tofu, drain out the water, and pat dry⁣
- If you can't find Thai basil, try it with sweet basil⁣
- Make sure to sauté ginger well until it starts to brown on the sides⁣
⁣
I hope you give this dish a try and have a wonderful day. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨❤️⁣

Mian Ge Da Tang😋, 面疙瘩汤 (Dough knot/drop soup) doesn't require any tools to make the noodles. All you need is some time and hand muscles💪🏼. This easy-to-make soup is so simple and delicious. The mushrooms and tomato soup are packed with umami savoriness. Slurp!🤤⁣
As usual, this video is a sneak peek of how it's done and don't forget to check the blog for tips and full instructions, yes, with a long video too💗.⁣
⁣
Full recipe: https://woonheng.com/ge-da-tang-dough-drop-soup/⁣
or search 'ge da tang' on woonheng.com⁣
or enjoy the full video on youtube on woonheng.com⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- Add the water in batches. Adding too much water at a fast pace will turn the dough into a large clump. I used a squeeze bottle.⁣
- Shake the bowl in a circular motion to combine the flour and water. ⁣
- Tomatoes need to be sauteed until they release their juice before adding the stock⁣
- Use your favorite vegetable stock or season your water with an umami seasoning such as yondu or mushrooms seasoning⁣
⁣
I hope you give this delicious dish a try, it's delicious and you get to work out too! Have a great weekend. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨💕⁣

Soybean pulp (okara) patty😋 is a wrap-up of my soybean series. Thank you so much for following along. It's really amazing how this little bean can do, right? Hope one of these recipes will be in your kitchen.🥰⁣
Ever since I shared my tofu skins and soymilk, many of you asked what to do with the pulp. You can actually use them in smoothies, compost, or turn them into soybean meal like almond meal but I wanted to make a savory dish out of it, thus the patties.👍🏼😁⁣
⁣
Full recipe instructions and long video: https://woonheng.com/soybean-pulp-okara-patty/⁣
or search 'soybean pulp patty'⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- Keep your pulp as fresh as possible⁣
- Create a somewhat wet paste so the patties are moist on the inside after they are cooked⁣
- You can add other vegetables to the patties⁣
- I continued to pan-fry, uncovered, to get a crisp outer layer⁣
- Sauce: I used sweet Thai chile sauce and added lime juice and chopped cilantro⁣
⁣
Hope you give this a try and have a wonderful weekend. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨💕⁣
